&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; TableItem[] updatedTableItems = table.getItems();<br />
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;                                        for(int k=0;<br />
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; k&lt;updatedTableItems.length; k++){<br />
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;   for(int i=0; i&lt;table.getColumnCount(); i++){<br />
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;           Button b = /* getButton at index [k][i] in the table */;<br />
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;<br />
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;   }                         }                                    What<br />
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; would go in the /* */ area?  table doesn't seem to give me<br />
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; methods that I can feed a row and a column index to and pull out the<br />
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; Button stored there.  Thanks for your help.<br />
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;<br />
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; Andy                                          <br />
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; Tom Schindl wrote:<br />
